The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for detecting and characterizing junctions in images, which is a common problem in the field of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new approach for matching indoor images, which involves using the anisotropic geometries of the detected junctions. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper uses a statistical model to estimate the scales of the junctions, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.RO (Robotics).
